  "text": "Focus groups were chosen since they are known to explicitly generate data via the process of group interaction [CITATION_1] . They also provided the opportunity for individuals to build on the answers of others in the group and in doing so generate new ideas [CITATION_2] . The interaction with others, in agreement or disagreement allowed participants to be exposed to a broader range of opinions. Furthermore, the group dynamic allowed more time for the participants to reflect on their opinion [CITATION_3] .",
